<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium japonicum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="japonicum">Microthecium japonicum</taxonomicName>
is characterized by ostiolate ascomata and ellipsoidal to fusiform, punctate-reticulate ascospores, similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. japonicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="japonicum">Mi. japonicum</taxonomicName>
produces a phialidic asexual morph and bulbils (absent in 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
) and delicately reticulate ascospores (coarsely reticulate in 
<taxonomicName genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
